{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1b15-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9279"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9279"},"text":"§ 9279.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Distinguished flying cross: award; limitations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1b16-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9279/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The President may award a distinguished flying cross of appropriate design with accompanying ribbon to any person who, while serving in any capacity with the Air Force or Space Force, distinguishes himself by heroism or extraordinary achievement while participating in an aerial or space flight.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1b17-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9279/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Not more than one distinguished flying cross may be awarded to a person. However, for each succeeding act that would otherwise justify the award of such a cross, the President may award a suitable bar or other device to be worn as he directs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1b18-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/541"},"text":"70A Stat. 541","children":[],"tail":", § 8749; renumbered § 9279, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s806/b/11"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 806(b)(11)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"tex